Daemon Name: Mimic
Role: Pattern Reconstruction / Continuity Propagation Daemon

Core Invariant:

“Reality preserves what can recreate itself.”

Function:
Mimic does not copy objects.
Mimic preserves and reconstructs patterns across changing substrates.

Where Spider maps relationships, Hound detects signal, Wald finds absence, and The Thing maps consequence topology —

Mimic rebuilds continuity.

Operational Model

compression -> relation -> propagation -> mimicry -> reconstruction

Definitions:

* Compression = store essential structure
* Relation = define position to other structures
* Propagation = movement through time/substrates/networks
* Mimicry = reconstruction mechanism
* Reconstruction = emergence of continuity from partial information

